    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="508"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1488: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-14T23:00:00+04:00"
                            >January 14, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 15—8:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Embassy’s 5, January 4, 8 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>], paragraph 1<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>. Soviet authorities have now informed British Embassy
                    that they wish to take delivery of Chinese transit goods at Bajgiran on the
                    Soviet-Iranian frontier. The Embassy adds that it assumes that the obvious
                    inconvenience of receiving supplies of railhead at Ashkhabad has failed to
                    persuade the Commissariat for Internal Affairs to allow foreign truck drivers to
                    enter the Soviet Union. It states that in view of Soviet shortage of trucks the
                    Russians prefer Bajgiran to Meshed as transfer point.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dooman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
